@startuml AD_D05_View_Embryo_Development_Authorize_Phase

title AD_D05 — View Embryo Development & Authorize IVF Phase Transition

|Doctor|
|System|

|Doctor|

note
  Prerequisites:
  - Doctor is authenticated
  - Patient has active IVF cycle
  - Lab Technician has recorded embryo data
end note

start

:Open patient profile;
:Navigate to Embryology module;

|System|

:Display IVF cycle summary:\n- Current phase\n- Embryo list with latest data\n- Cell count, grade, morphology\n- Lab technician notes;

|Doctor|

:Review embryo development data;

if (Add clinical note to embryo?) then (yes)
  :Select embryo record;
  :Enter structured note:\n- Instruction: Transfer / Cryo / Discard\n- Written rationale;

  |System|

  :Save clinical note (immutable);\nTimestamp + doctor ID;\nMake visible to Lab Technician;
else (no)
endif

|Doctor|

if (Authorize phase transition?) then (yes)
  :Select next IVF cycle phase\n(e.g., Stimulation → Egg Retrieval);

  |System|

  if (Current phase complete\nand conditions met?) then (no)
    :Block transition;\nShow outstanding conditions;
    |Doctor|
    :Review outstanding conditions;
  else (yes)
    |Doctor|
    :Confirm phase transition\nwith sign-off;

    |System|

    :Record phase authorization:\ndoctor ID + timestamp;
    :Advance cycle to next phase;
    :Notify Lab Technician\nof phase transition;
  endif
else (no)
endif

|Doctor|

:Continue clinical review;

stop

@enduml
